    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa84619e_94db604a",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 249,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T20:14:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nope.\nThis source says 64-bit objects should have 8-byte alignment, 32-bit, 4-byte alignment:\nhttp://www.sco.com/developers/gabi/latest/ch5.pheader.html\n\nThis source says both 64-bit and 32-bit objects have 4-byte alignment:\nhttps://docs.oracle.com/cd/E23824_01/html/819-0690/chapter6-18048.html\n\nObservation so far (and the kernel header\u0027s definition for Elf64_Nhdr) says 64-bit objects use 4-byte aligned notes.",
      "parentUuid": "e8cdd882_f0caa581",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 249,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 249,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e46e3ab6_7335430d",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 249,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T21:09:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Nope.\n\u003e This source says 64-bit objects should have 8-byte alignment, 32-bit, 4-byte alignment:\n\u003e http://www.sco.com/developers/gabi/latest/ch5.pheader.html\n\u003e \n\u003e This source says both 64-bit and 32-bit objects have 4-byte alignment:\n\u003e https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E23824_01/html/819-0690/chapter6-18048.html\n\u003e \n\u003e Observation so far (and the kernel header\u0027s definition for Elf64_Nhdr) says 64-bit objects use 4-byte aligned notes.\n\nI asked because line 238 sets align to 8 with NhdrType \u003d Elf64_Nhdr. Is that wrong?",
      "parentUuid": "fa84619e_94db604a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 249,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 249,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9161558_3e3c31a2",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 249,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T21:31:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For Linux, Elf64_Nhdr and Elf32_Nhdr are equivalent. Both use 32-bit types.\nI check anyways, in case some other OS (Fuchsia) does use 64-bit types.\nI\u0027ll update the comment to specify Linux, specifically, uses 4-byte alignment.",
      "parentUuid": "e46e3ab6_7335430d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 249,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 249,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "122209e5_c8025518",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 249,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T22:05:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e For Linux, Elf64_Nhdr and Elf32_Nhdr are equivalent. Both use 32-bit types.\n\u003e I check anyways, in case some other OS (Fuchsia) does use 64-bit types.\n\u003e I\u0027ll update the comment to specify Linux, specifically, uses 4-byte alignment.\n\nMy brain fart: Elf32_Word and Elf64_Word are still both uint32_t, not uint32_t/uint64_t.\n\nBut I was also led astray by NoteReader::type_filter_ being uint64_t. It seems that that’s too big, and that it and all related types should actually be uint32_t.",
      "parentUuid": "a9161558_3e3c31a2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 249,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 249,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "288c363f_bd3a8dbb",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 249,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T22:34:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "uint32_t should be sufficient for Linux, but I left it as uint64_t in case something does use 64-bit entries and to avoid having to templatize the NoteReader or NextNote.\n\nI could also make it a uint32_t with a static_assert that Elf*_Nhdr::n_namesz is 4-bytes and change it should we find something that uses 8-byte types.",
      "parentUuid": "122209e5_c8025518",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 249,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 249,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "559e85e3_28da0970",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 249,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T22:59:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e uint32_t should be sufficient for Linux, but I left it as uint64_t in case something does use 64-bit entries and to avoid having to templatize the NoteReader or NextNote.\n\nSeems like that’d be contrary to the ELF spec, which does say “4 bytes” for this.\n\n\u003e I could also make it a uint32_t with a static_assert that Elf*_Nhdr::n_namesz is 4-bytes and change it should we find something that uses 8-byte types.\n\nThat’s probably the best approach, let’s do it.",
      "parentUuid": "288c363f_bd3a8dbb",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 249,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 249,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
