        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T03:22:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This comment is terrifying. Is this really what other readers do?",
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cdc5d707_3560a5ec",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 250,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T20:14:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It doesn\u0027t look like readelf or GDB do any special handling when reading from note segments. They assume all the notes are 4-byte aligned so I suspect they would fail if they tried to read sequential notes where the first note is mis-aligned. Normally, they read notes using the section header table, which gives the start address of each note individually. They only fall back to the program header table for core files, but I think .note.android.ident wouldn\u0027t normally end up there.",
      "parentUuid": "a9353176_b31fc86d",
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b0ea6ba6_6ec1f1d7",
        "filename": "snapshot/elf/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 250,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T21:09:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e It doesn\u0027t look like readelf or GDB do any special handling when reading from note segments. They assume all the notes are 4-byte aligned so I suspect they would fail if they tried to read sequential notes where the first note is mis-aligned. Normally, they read notes using the section header table, which gives the start address of each note individually. They only fall back to the program header table for core files, but I think .note.android.ident wouldn\u0027t normally end up there.\n\nRather than inferring the alignment, can we use ElfN_Phdr::p_align?",
      "parentUuid": "cdc5d707_3560a5ec",
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
